8. The Municipal Accountant recognize as inventory purchases of supplies instead of expense;
9. The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer prepare and maintain supplies ledger card and stock card respectively, and reconcile their records regularly; and
10. Use the RIS and SSMI for effective inventory management.

We recommended compliance on the following:
1. The Municipal Treasurer shall file a request for disposal of unserviceable properties supported with necessary documents needed for technical evaluation and appraisal;
2. Likewise, the Municipal Treasurer shall also coordinate with the Municipal Accountant for proper classification of the unserviceable items to Other Asset Account.

We recommended that the Municipality adhere strictly with the Civil Service Commission guidelines on the grant of PRAISE. Likewise, complete supporting documents should be observed by submitting the following:
a) Copy of the composition of the PRAISE Committee;
b) Copy of the Municipality’s CSC Approved PRAISE;
c) Performance Ratings of each permanent officers and employees;
d) Basis for the amount given;
e) Criteria in granting the PRAISE Bonus as recommended by the PRAISE Committee;
f) List of Savings and Monetary Awards earned / generated during CY 2015 and relevant supporting documents;
g) Evaluation reports or any documentation recognizing the productivity, creativeness, innovation made/or ethical behavior of employees or group of employees making them eligible for the PRAISE; and
h) Specific legal basis which allows the grant of the incentives in the absence of the above requirements, otherwise the incentives granted be refunded immediately.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

Municipal Agriculture Officer to expedite the use of the P5, 060,037.00 for the five BUB Projects under his supervision so that immediate goal of the project could be achieved;

Municipal Engineer to fast track the implementation of the Potable Water Supply System;

BUB Focal Person to closely monitor the implementation of all BUB projects so that the optimum goal of inclusive growth and poverty reduction could be fully attained; and

Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to immediately refund/remit the excess BUB project funds to the source national government agencies to avoid possible loss or misuse.

